description: "Before the start of recorded history, the world endured a long period without a calendar or written record. This era is remembered chiefly through fragmentary oral tradition: scattered monster battles fought by survivors and adventurers, and the first informal trade between settlements that would later grow into cities. The current calendar begins after this period, with [[The Start of Tracked History]] in Year 1."
